1
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:09,345
The Vaishanava's strategy 
is to remember

2
00:00:09,345 --> 00:00:14,900
or take shelter 
of the devotee of Kṛṣṇa.

3
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:18,176
[Devotee's Strategy]

4
00:00:18,256 --> 00:00:27,306
Because, 
ahaṁ bhakta-parādhīno
hy asvatantra iva dvija
sādhubhir grasta-hṛdayo
bhaktair bhakta-jana-priyaḥ 
[SB: 9.4.63]

5
00:00:27,391 --> 00:00:31,496
The devotees are always 
in the heart of Kṛṣṇa.

6
00:00:31,586 --> 00:00:33,066
If we factor in

7
00:00:33,066 --> 00:00:36,795
ye yathā māḿ prapadyante
tāḿs tathaiva bhajāmy aham 
[BG: 4.11]

8
00:00:36,795 --> 00:00:44,135
Kṛṣṇa is saying, 
"I reciprocate devotion."

9
00:00:44,227 --> 00:00:47,134
So, if devotees are incessantly—

10
00:00:47,134 --> 00:00:50,621
and we're talking here 
about substantial devotees,—

11
00:00:50,621 --> 00:00:56,008
they are incessantly in remembrance of Kṛṣṇa,

12
00:00:56,906 --> 00:01:02,856
śrotavyaḥ kīrtitavyaś ca
smartavyaś cecchatābhayam
[SB: 2.1.5]

13
00:01:02,875 --> 00:01:07,844
They're always thinking of the lotus feet [of Kṛṣṇa],
that's why they're qualified in that way.

14
00:01:07,844 --> 00:01:11,384
So, as they're totaly... 
they never stop thinking of Kṛṣṇa,

15
00:01:11,384 --> 00:01:14,654
Kṛṣṇa never stops 
thinking of them.

